      <div xml:id="NA16-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu poruḷ kaṭaikkūṭiya (EN, ET: kaṭaikūṭṭiya) neñciṉai nerukkit talaivaṉ (EN, ET: neruṅki; ET: talaimakaṉ) celavu aḻuṅkiyatu. (EV: poruḷmēṟ ceṉṟa uḷḷattiṉai iṭitturaittut talaivaṉ celavu tavirntatu.)</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how HE prevents going, directed to [his] heart that covetted wealth. (EV: This is how HE hinders [his] heart, that went after wealth, in going.)</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA16">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            puṇariṟ puṇarātu poruḷē poruḷvayiṟ</l>
<l>            piriyiṟ puṇarātu puṇarvē yāyiṭaic</l>
<l>            celliṉuñ cellā yāyiṉu nallataṟ</l>
<l>            kuriyai vāḻiyeṉ ṉeñcē poruḷē</l>
<l>            vāṭāp pūviṉ poykai nāppa </l>
<l>            ṇōṭumīṉ vaḻiyiṟ keṭuva yāṉē</l>
<l>            viḻunīr viyalakan tūṇi yāka</l>
<l>            veḻumā ṇaḷakkum viḻuneti peṟiṉuṅ</l>
<l>            kaṉaṅkuḻaik kamartta cēyari maḻaikka</l>
<l>            ṇamarntiṉitu nōkkamoṭu cekuttaṉa </l>
<l>            ḷeṉṉaiya vākuka vāḻiya poruḷē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>If uniting [with her, it means] not uniting with wealth. If separating</l>
<l>for wealth, [it means] not having union [with her].</l>
<l rend="indent4">In beween these [two],</l>
<l>whether you go or whether you don't go, you are worthy</l>
<l>of the good, live, my heart.</l>
<l rend="indent3">Wealth,</l>
<l>it gets<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">keṭuva</term>, as well as <term xml:lang="ta">ākuka</term> in line 11, are n.pl., so poruḷ is to be understood as a plural.</note> lost like the paths of the fish [do],</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the middle of the pond with unfading flowers.</l>
<l rend="indent3">As for me,</l>
<l rend="indent2">even if I obtained an excellent treasure measuring seven times<note place="foot">For <term xml:lang="ta">māṇ</term> in this function, see note on NA 12.5.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">what is the measure of the wide interior of the excellent water,</l>
<l>she would destroy [me] by a sweetly lingering look of [her]</l>
<l rend="indent">red-lined rain eyes, which were at strife with the thick earrings.</l>
<l>What might become of it? – let it live, wealth.</l>
            
        
</lg>
